http://schema.org/about.comment: The subject matter of the content.
http://schema.org/about.label: about

http://schema.org/abridged.comment: Indicates whether the book is an abridged edition.
http://schema.org/abridged.label: abridged

http://schema.org/accelerationTime.comment:
The time needed to accelerate the vehicle from a given start velocity to a given target velocity.

Typical unit code(s): SEC for seconds

  • Note: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for seconds/0..100 km/h or seconds/0..60 mph. Simply use "SEC" for seconds and indicate the velocities in the name of the QuantitativeValue, or use valueReference with a QuantitativeValue of 0..60 mph or 0..100 km/h to specify the reference speeds.
http://schema.org/accelerationTime.label: accelerationTime

http://schema.org/acceptedAnswer.comment: The answer that has been accepted as best, typically on a Question/Answer site. Sites vary in their selection mechanisms, e.g. drawing on community opinion and/or the view of the Question author.
http://schema.org/acceptedAnswer.label: acceptedAnswer

http://schema.org/acceptedOffer.comment: The offer(s) -- e.g., product, quantity and price combinations -- included in the order.
http://schema.org/acceptedOffer.label: acceptedOffer

http://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.comment: The payment method(s) accepted by seller for this offer.
http://schema.org/acceptedPaymentMethod.label: acceptedPaymentMethod

http://schema.org/acceptsReservations.comment: Indicates whether a FoodEstablishment accepts reservations. Values can be Boolean, an URL at which reservations can be made or (for backwards compatibility) the strings Yes or No.
http://schema.org/acceptsReservations.label: acceptsReservations

http://schema.org/accessCode.comment: Password, PIN, or access code needed for delivery (e.g. from a locker).
http://schema.org/accessCode.label: accessCode

http://schema.org/accessMode.comment: The human sensory perceptual system or cognitive faculty through which a person may process or perceive information. Expected values include: auditory, tactile, textual, visual, colorDependent, chartOnVisual, chemOnVisual, diagramOnVisual, mathOnVisual, musicOnVisual, textOnVisual.
http://schema.org/accessMode.label: accessMode

http://schema.org/accessModeSufficient.comment: A list of single or combined accessModes that are sufficient to understand all the intellectual content of a resource. Expected values include:  auditory, tactile, textual, visual.
http://schema.org/accessModeSufficient.label: accessModeSufficient

http://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.comment: Indicates that the resource is compatible with the referenced accessibility API (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
http://schema.org/accessibilityAPI.label: accessibilityAPI

http://schema.org/accessibilityControl.comment: Identifies input methods that are sufficient to fully control the described resource (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
http://schema.org/accessibilityControl.label: accessibilityControl

http://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.comment: Content features of the resource, such as accessible media, alternatives and supported enhancements for accessibility (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
http://schema.org/accessibilityFeature.label: accessibilityFeature

http://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.comment: A characteristic of the described resource that is physiologically dangerous to some users. Related to WCAG 2.0 guideline 2.3 (WebSchemas wiki lists possible values).
http://schema.org/accessibilityHazard.label: accessibilityHazard

http://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.comment: A human-readable summary of specific accessibility features or deficiencies, consistent with the other accessibility metadata but expressing subtleties such as "short descriptions are present but long descriptions will be needed for non-visual users" or "short descriptions are present and no long descriptions are needed."
http://schema.org/accessibilitySummary.label: accessibilitySummary

http://schema.org/accountId.comment: The identifier for the account the payment will be applied to.
http://schema.org/accountId.label: accountId

http://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.comment: A minimum amount that has to be paid in every month.
http://schema.org/accountMinimumInflow.label: accountMinimumInflow

http://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.comment: An overdraft is an extension of credit from a lending institution when an account reaches zero. An overdraft allows the individual to continue withdrawing money even if the account has no funds in it. Basically the bank allows people to borrow a set amount of money.
http://schema.org/accountOverdraftLimit.label: accountOverdraftLimit

http://schema.org/accountablePerson.comment: Specifies the Person that is legally accountable for the CreativeWork.
http://schema.org/accountablePerson.label: accountablePerson

http://schema.org/acquiredFrom.comment: The organization or person from which the product was acquired.
http://schema.org/acquiredFrom.label: acquiredFrom

http://schema.org/acrissCode.comment: The ACRISS Car Classification Code is a code used by many car rental companies, for classifying vehicles. ACRISS stands for Association of Car Rental Industry Systems and Standards.
http://schema.org/acrissCode.label: acrissCode

http://schema.org/action.comment: Obsolete term for muscleAction. Not to be confused with potentialAction.
http://schema.org/action.label: action

http://schema.org/actionApplication.comment: An application that can complete the request.
http://schema.org/actionApplication.label: actionApplication

http://schema.org/actionOption.comment: A sub property of object. The options subject to this action.
http://schema.org/actionOption.label: actionOption

http://schema.org/actionPlatform.comment: The high level platform(s) where the Action can be performed for the given URL. To specify a specific application or operating system instance, use actionApplication.
http://schema.org/actionPlatform.label: actionPlatform

http://schema.org/actionStatus.comment: Indicates the current disposition of the Action.
http://schema.org/actionStatus.label: actionStatus

http://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPoli.comment: For a NewsMediaOrganization or other news-related Organization, a statement about public engagement activities (for news media, the newsroom’s), including involving the public - digitally or otherwise -- in coverage decisions, reporting and activities after publication.
http://schema.org/actionableFeedbackPoli.label: actionableFeedbackPolicy

http://schema.org/activeIngredient.comment: An active ingredient, typically chemical compounds and/or biologic substances.
http://schema.org/activeIngredient.label: activeIngredient

http://schema.org/activityDuration.comment: Length of time to engage in the activity.
http://schema.org/activityDuration.label: activityDuration

http://schema.org/activityFrequency.comment: How often one should engage in the activity.
http://schema.org/activityFrequency.label: activityFrequency

http://schema.org/actor.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
http://schema.org/actor.label: actor

http://schema.org/actors.comment: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.
http://schema.org/actors.label: actors

http://schema.org/addOn.comment: An additional offer that can only be obtained in combination with the first base offer (e.g. supplements and extensions that are available for a surcharge).
http://schema.org/addOn.label: addOn

http://schema.org/additionalName.comment: An additional name for a Person, can be used for a middle name.
http://schema.org/additionalName.label: additionalName

http://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGues.comment: If responding yes, the number of guests who will attend in addition to the invitee.
http://schema.org/additionalNumberOfGues.label: additionalNumberOfGuests

http://schema.org/additionalProperty.comment:
A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.

Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.
http://schema.org/additionalProperty.label: additionalProperty

http://schema.org/additionalType.comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
http://schema.org/additionalType.label: additionalType

http://schema.org/additionalVariable.comment: Any additional component of the exercise prescription that may need to be articulated to the patient. This may include the order of exercises, the number of repetitions of movement, quantitative distance, progressions over time, etc.
http://schema.org/additionalVariable.label: additionalVariable

http://schema.org/addressCountry.comment: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
http://schema.org/addressCountry.label: addressCountry

http://schema.org/addressLocality.comment: The locality. For example, Mountain View.
http://schema.org/addressLocality.label: addressLocality

http://schema.org/administrationRoute.comment: A route by which this drug may be administered, e.g. 'oral'.
http://schema.org/administrationRoute.label: administrationRoute

http://schema.org/advanceBookingRequirem.comment: The amount of time that is required between accepting the offer and the actual usage of the resource or service.
http://schema.org/advanceBookingRequirem.label: advanceBookingRequirement

http://schema.org/adverseOutcome.comment: A possible complication and/or side effect of this therapy. If it is known that an adverse outcome is serious (resulting in death, disability, or permanent damage; requiring hospitalization; or is otherwise life-threatening or requires immediate medical attention), tag it as a seriouseAdverseOutcome instead.
http://schema.org/adverseOutcome.label: adverseOutcome

http://schema.org/affectedBy.comment: Drugs that affect the test's results.
http://schema.org/affectedBy.label: affectedBy

http://schema.org/affiliation.comment: An organization that this person is affiliated with. For example, a school/university, a club, or a team.
http://schema.org/affiliation.label: affiliation

http://schema.org/afterMedia.comment: A media object representing the circumstances after performing this direction.
http://schema.org/afterMedia.label: afterMedia

http://schema.org/agent.comment: The direct performer or driver of the action (animate or inanimate). e.g. John wrote a book.
http://schema.org/agent.label: agent

http://schema.org/aggregateRating.comment: The overall rating, based on a collection of reviews or ratings, of the item.
http://schema.org/aggregateRating.label: aggregateRating

http://schema.org/albumProductionType.comment: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.
http://schema.org/albumProductionType.label: albumProductionType

http://schema.org/albumReleaseType.comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.
http://schema.org/albumReleaseType.label: albumReleaseType

http://schema.org/alcoholWarning.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of alcohol while taking this drug.
http://schema.org/alcoholWarning.label: alcoholWarning

http://schema.org/algorithm.comment: The algorithm or rules to follow to compute the score.
http://schema.org/algorithm.label: algorithm

http://schema.org/alignmentType.comment: A category of alignment between the learning resource and the framework node. Recommended values include: 'assesses', 'teaches', 'requires', 'textComplexity', 'readingLevel', 'educationalSubject', and 'educationalLevel'.
http://schema.org/alignmentType.label: alignmentType

http://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.comment: A secondary title of the CreativeWork.
http://schema.org/alternativeHeadline.label: alternativeHeadline

http://schema.org/alumniOf.comment: An organization that the person is an alumni of.
http://schema.org/alumniOf.label: alumniOf

http://schema.org/amenityFeature.comment: An amenity feature (e.g. a characteristic or service) of the Accommodation. This generic property does not make a statement about whether the feature is included in an offer for the main accommodation or available at extra costs.
http://schema.org/amenityFeature.label: amenityFeature

http://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.comment: The quantity of the goods included in the offer.
http://schema.org/amountOfThisGood.label: amountOfThisGood

http://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.comment: The annual rate that is charged for borrowing (or made by investing), expressed as a single percentage number that represents the actual yearly cost of funds over the term of a loan. This includes any fees or additional costs associated with the transaction.
http://schema.org/annualPercentageRate.label: annualPercentageRate

http://schema.org/answerCount.comment: The number of answers this question has received.
http://schema.org/answerCount.label: answerCount

http://schema.org/antagonist.comment: The muscle whose action counteracts the specified muscle.
http://schema.org/antagonist.label: antagonist

http://schema.org/applicableLocation.comment: The location in which the status applies.
http://schema.org/applicableLocation.label: applicableLocation

http://schema.org/application.comment: An application that can complete the request.
http://schema.org/application.label: application

http://schema.org/applicationCategory.comment: Type of software application, e.g. 'Game, Multimedia'.
http://schema.org/applicationCategory.label: applicationCategory

http://schema.org/applicationSubCategory.comment: Subcategory of the application, e.g. 'Arcade Game'.
http://schema.org/applicationSubCategory.label: applicationSubCategory

http://schema.org/applicationSuite.comment: The name of the application suite to which the application belongs (e.g. Excel belongs to Office).
http://schema.org/applicationSuite.label: applicationSuite

http://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMetho.comment: The delivery method(s) to which the delivery charge or payment charge specification applies.
http://schema.org/appliesToDeliveryMetho.label: appliesToDeliveryMethod

http://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMethod.comment: The payment method(s) to which the payment charge specification applies.
http://schema.org/appliesToPaymentMethod.label: appliesToPaymentMethod

http://schema.org/area.comment: The area within which users can expect to reach the broadcast service.
http://schema.org/area.label: area

http://schema.org/areaServed.comment: The geographic area where a service or offered item is provided.
http://schema.org/areaServed.label: areaServed

http://schema.org/arrivalAirport.comment: The airport where the flight terminates.
http://schema.org/arrivalAirport.label: arrivalAirport

http://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.comment: The stop or station from which the bus arrives.
http://schema.org/arrivalBusStop.label: arrivalBusStop

http://schema.org/arrivalGate.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival gate.
http://schema.org/arrivalGate.label: arrivalGate

http://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.comment: The platform where the train arrives.
http://schema.org/arrivalPlatform.label: arrivalPlatform

http://schema.org/arrivalStation.comment: The station where the train trip ends.
http://schema.org/arrivalStation.label: arrivalStation

http://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.comment: Identifier of the flight's arrival terminal.
http://schema.org/arrivalTerminal.label: arrivalTerminal

http://schema.org/artEdition.comment: The number of copies when multiple copies of a piece of artwork are produced - e.g. for a limited edition of 20 prints, 'artEdition' refers to the total number of copies (in this example "20").
http://schema.org/artEdition.label: artEdition

http://schema.org/artMedium.comment: The material used. (e.g. Oil, Watercolour, Acrylic, Linoprint, Marble, Cyanotype, Digital, Lithograph, DryPoint, Intaglio, Pastel, Woodcut, Pencil, Mixed Media, etc.)
http://schema.org/artMedium.label: artMedium

http://schema.org/arterialBranch.comment: The branches that comprise the arterial structure.
http://schema.org/arterialBranch.label: arterialBranch

http://schema.org/artform.comment: e.g. Painting, Drawing, Sculpture, Print, Photograph, Assemblage, Collage, etc.
http://schema.org/artform.label: artform

http://schema.org/articleBody.comment: The actual body of the article.
http://schema.org/articleBody.label: articleBody

http://schema.org/articleSection.comment: Articles may belong to one or more 'sections' in a magazine or newspaper, such as Sports, Lifestyle, etc.
http://schema.org/articleSection.label: articleSection

http://schema.org/artist.comment:
The primary artist for a work
    in a medium other than pencils or digital line art--for example, if the
    primary artwork is done in watercolors or digital paints.
http://schema.org/artist.label: artist

http://schema.org/artworkSurface.comment: The supporting materials for the artwork, e.g. Canvas, Paper, Wood, Board, etc.
http://schema.org/artworkSurface.label: artworkSurface

http://schema.org/aspect.comment: An aspect of medical practice that is considered on the page, such as 'diagnosis', 'treatment', 'causes', 'prognosis', 'etiology', 'epidemiology', etc.
http://schema.org/aspect.label: aspect

http://schema.org/assembly.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.
http://schema.org/assembly.label: assembly

http://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.comment: The anatomy of the underlying organ system or structures associated with this entity.
http://schema.org/associatedAnatomy.label: associatedAnatomy

http://schema.org/associatedArticle.comment: A NewsArticle associated with the Media Object.
http://schema.org/associatedArticle.label: associatedArticle

http://schema.org/associatedMedia.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for encoding.
http://schema.org/associatedMedia.label: associatedMedia

http://schema.org/associatedPathophysiol.comment: If applicable, a description of the pathophysiology associated with the anatomical system, including potential abnormal changes in the mechanical, physical, and biochemical functions of the system.
http://schema.org/associatedPathophysiol.label: associatedPathophysiology

http://schema.org/athlete.comment: A person that acts as performing member of a sports team; a player as opposed to a coach.
http://schema.org/athlete.label: athlete

http://schema.org/attendee.comment: A person or organization attending the event.
http://schema.org/attendee.label: attendee

http://schema.org/audience.comment: An intended audience, i.e. a group for whom something was created.
http://schema.org/audience.label: audience

http://schema.org/audienceType.comment: The target group associated with a given audience (e.g. veterans, car owners, musicians, etc.).
http://schema.org/audienceType.label: audienceType

http://schema.org/author.comment: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.
http://schema.org/author.label: author

http://schema.org/availability.comment: The availability of this item—for example In stock, Out of stock, Pre-order, etc.
http://schema.org/availability.label: availability

http://schema.org/availabilityEnds.comment: The end of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.
http://schema.org/availabilityEnds.label: availabilityEnds

http://schema.org/availabilityStarts.comment: The beginning of the availability of the product or service included in the offer.
http://schema.org/availabilityStarts.label: availabilityStarts

http://schema.org/availableAtOrFrom.comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).
http://schema.org/availableAtOrFrom.label: availableAtOrFrom

http://schema.org/availableChannel.comment: A means of accessing the service (e.g. a phone bank, a web site, a location, etc.).
http://schema.org/availableChannel.label: availableChannel

http://schema.org/availableDeliveryMetho.comment: The delivery method(s) available for this offer.
http://schema.org/availableDeliveryMetho.label: availableDeliveryMethod

http://schema.org/availableFrom.comment: When the item is available for pickup from the store, locker, etc.
http://schema.org/availableFrom.label: availableFrom

http://schema.org/availableIn.comment: The location in which the strength is available.
http://schema.org/availableIn.label: availableIn

http://schema.org/availableLanguage.comment: A language someone may use with or at the item, service or place. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also inLanguage
http://schema.org/availableLanguage.label: availableLanguage

http://schema.org/availableOnDevice.comment: Device required to run the application. Used in cases where a specific make/model is required to run the application.
http://schema.org/availableOnDevice.label: availableOnDevice

http://schema.org/availableService.comment: A medical service available from this provider.
http://schema.org/availableService.label: availableService

http://schema.org/availableStrength.comment: An available dosage strength for the drug.
http://schema.org/availableStrength.label: availableStrength

http://schema.org/availableTest.comment: A diagnostic test or procedure offered by this lab.
http://schema.org/availableTest.label: availableTest

http://schema.org/availableThrough.comment: After this date, the item will no longer be available for pickup.
http://schema.org/availableThrough.label: availableThrough

http://schema.org/award.comment: An award won by or for this item.
http://schema.org/award.label: award

http://schema.org/awards.comment: Awards won by or for this item.
http://schema.org/awards.label: awards

http://schema.org/awayTeam.comment: The away team in a sports event.
http://schema.org/awayTeam.label: awayTeam

http://schema.org/background.comment: Descriptive information establishing a historical perspective on the supplement. May include the rationale for the name, the population where the supplement first came to prominence, etc.
http://schema.org/background.label: background

http://schema.org/bankAccountType.comment: The type of a bank account.
http://schema.org/bankAccountType.label: bankAccountType

http://schema.org/baseSalary.comment: The base salary of the job or of an employee in an EmployeeRole.
http://schema.org/baseSalary.label: baseSalary

http://schema.org/bccRecipient.comment: A sub property of recipient. The recipient blind copied on a message.
http://schema.org/bccRecipient.label: bccRecipient

http://schema.org/bed.comment:
The type of bed or beds included in the accommodation. For the single case of just one bed of a certain type, you use bed directly with a text.
      If you want to indicate the quantity of a certain kind of bed, use an instance of BedDetails. For more detailed information, use the amenityFeature property.
http://schema.org/bed.label: bed

http://schema.org/beforeMedia.comment: A media object representing the circumstances before performing this direction.
http://schema.org/beforeMedia.label: beforeMedia

http://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.comment: A bank or bank’s branch, financial institution or international financial institution operating the beneficiary’s bank account or releasing funds for the beneficiary
http://schema.org/beneficiaryBank.label: beneficiaryBank

http://schema.org/benefits.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.
http://schema.org/benefits.label: benefits

http://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.comment: The URL that goes directly to the summary of benefits and coverage for the specific standard plan or plan variation.
http://schema.org/benefitsSummaryUrl.label: benefitsSummaryUrl

http://schema.org/bestRating.comment: The highest value allowed in this rating system. If bestRating is omitted, 5 is assumed.
http://schema.org/bestRating.label: bestRating

http://schema.org/billingAddress.comment: The billing address for the order.
http://schema.org/billingAddress.label: billingAddress

http://schema.org/billingIncrement.comment: This property specifies the minimal quantity and rounding increment that will be the basis for the billing. The unit of measurement is specified by the unitCode property.
http://schema.org/billingIncrement.label: billingIncrement

http://schema.org/billingPeriod.comment: The time interval used to compute the invoice.
http://schema.org/billingPeriod.label: billingPeriod

http://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.comment: The biomechanical properties of the bone.
http://schema.org/biomechnicalClass.label: biomechnicalClass

http://schema.org/birthPlace.comment: The place where the person was born.
http://schema.org/birthPlace.label: birthPlace

http://schema.org/bitrate.comment: The bitrate of the media object.
http://schema.org/bitrate.label: bitrate

http://schema.org/blogPost.comment: A posting that is part of this blog.
http://schema.org/blogPost.label: blogPost

http://schema.org/blogPosts.comment: The postings that are part of this blog.
http://schema.org/blogPosts.label: blogPosts

http://schema.org/bloodSupply.comment: The blood vessel that carries blood from the heart to the muscle.
http://schema.org/bloodSupply.label: bloodSupply

http://schema.org/boardingGroup.comment: The airline-specific indicator of boarding order / preference.
http://schema.org/boardingGroup.label: boardingGroup

http://schema.org/boardingPolicy.comment: The type of boarding policy used by the airline (e.g. zone-based or group-based).
http://schema.org/boardingPolicy.label: boardingPolicy

http://schema.org/bodyLocation.comment: Location in the body of the anatomical structure.
http://schema.org/bodyLocation.label: bodyLocation

http://schema.org/bodyType.comment: Indicates the design and body style of the vehicle (e.g. station wagon, hatchback, etc.).
http://schema.org/bodyType.label: bodyType

http://schema.org/bookingAgent.comment: 'bookingAgent' is an out-dated term indicating a 'broker' that serves as a booking agent.
http://schema.org/bookingAgent.label: bookingAgent

http://schema.org/bookingTime.comment: The date and time the reservation was booked.
http://schema.org/bookingTime.label: bookingTime

http://schema.org/borrower.comment: A sub property of participant. The person that borrows the object being lent.
http://schema.org/borrower.label: borrower

http://schema.org/box.comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.
http://schema.org/box.label: box

http://schema.org/branch.comment: The branches that delineate from the nerve bundle. Not to be confused with branchOf.
http://schema.org/branch.label: branch

http://schema.org/branchCode.comment:
A short textual code (also called "store code") that uniquely identifies a place of business. The code is typically assigned by the parentOrganization and used in structured URLs.

For example, in the URL http://www.starbucks.co.uk/store-locator/etc/detail/3047 the code "3047" is a branchCode for a particular branch.
http://schema.org/branchCode.label: branchCode

http://schema.org/branchOf.comment: The larger organization that this local business is a branch of, if any. Not to be confused with (anatomical)branch.
http://schema.org/branchOf.label: branchOf

http://schema.org/brand.comment: The brand(s) associated with a product or service, or the brand(s) maintained by an organization or business person.
http://schema.org/brand.label: brand

http://schema.org/breadcrumb.comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.
http://schema.org/breadcrumb.label: breadcrumb

http://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to this drug's use by breastfeeding mothers.
http://schema.org/breastfeedingWarning.label: breastfeedingWarning

http://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.comment: The media network(s) whose content is broadcast on this station.
http://schema.org/broadcastAffiliateOf.label: broadcastAffiliateOf

http://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.comment: The unique address by which the BroadcastService can be identified in a provider lineup. In US, this is typically a number.
http://schema.org/broadcastChannelId.label: broadcastChannelId

http://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.comment: The name displayed in the channel guide. For many US affiliates, it is the network name.
http://schema.org/broadcastDisplayName.label: broadcastDisplayName

http://schema.org/broadcastFrequency.comment: The frequency used for over-the-air broadcasts. Numeric values or simple ranges e.g. 87-99. In addition a shortcut idiom is supported for frequences of AM and FM radio channels, e.g. "87 FM".
http://schema.org/broadcastFrequency.label: broadcastFrequency

http://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyValu.comment: The frequency in MHz for a particular broadcast.
http://schema.org/broadcastFrequencyValu.label: broadcastFrequencyValue

http://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.comment: The event being broadcast such as a sporting event or awards ceremony.
http://schema.org/broadcastOfEvent.label: broadcastOfEvent

http://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.comment: The type of service required to have access to the channel (e.g. Standard or Premium).
http://schema.org/broadcastServiceTier.label: broadcastServiceTier

http://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.comment: The timezone in ISO 8601 format for which the service bases its broadcasts
http://schema.org/broadcastTimezone.label: broadcastTimezone

http://schema.org/broadcaster.comment: The organization owning or operating the broadcast service.
http://schema.org/broadcaster.label: broadcaster

http://schema.org/broker.comment: An entity that arranges for an exchange between a buyer and a seller.  In most cases a broker never acquires or releases ownership of a product or service involved in an exchange.  If it is not clear whether an entity is a broker, seller, or buyer, the latter two terms are preferred.
http://schema.org/broker.label: broker

http://schema.org/browserRequirements.comment: Specifies browser requirements in human-readable text. For example, 'requires HTML5 support'.
http://schema.org/browserRequirements.label: browserRequirements

http://schema.org/busName.comment: The name of the bus (e.g. Bolt Express).

http://schema.org/eligibleRegion.label: eligibleRegion

http://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVol.comment: The transaction volume, in a monetary unit, for which the offer or price specification is valid, e.g. for indicating a minimal purchasing volume, to express free shipping above a certain order volume, or to limit the acceptance of credit cards to purchases to a certain minimal amount.
http://schema.org/eligibleTransactionVol.label: eligibleTransactionVolume

http://schema.org/embedUrl.comment: A URL pointing to a player for a specific video. In general, this is the information in the src element of an embed tag and should not be the same as the content of the loc tag.
http://schema.org/embedUrl.label: embedUrl

http://schema.org/emissionsCO2.comment: The CO2 emissions in g/km. When used in combination with a QuantitativeValue, put "g/km" into the unitText property of that value, since there is no UN/CEFACT Common Code for "g/km".
http://schema.org/emissionsCO2.label: emissionsCO2

http://schema.org/employmentType.comment: Type of employment (e.g. full-time, part-time, contract, temporary, seasonal, internship).
http://schema.org/employmentType.label: employmentType

http://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.comment: The CreativeWork encoded by this media object.
http://schema.org/encodesCreativeWork.label: encodesCreativeWork

http://schema.org/encoding.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork. This property is a synonym for associatedMedia.
http://schema.org/encoding.label: encoding

http://schema.org/encodingType.comment: The supported encoding type(s) for an EntryPoint request.
http://schema.org/encodingType.label: encodingType

http://schema.org/encodings.comment: A media object that encodes this CreativeWork.
http://schema.org/encodings.label: encodings

http://schema.org/endDate.comment: The end date and time of the item (in ISO 8601 date format).
http://schema.org/endDate.label: endDate

http://schema.org/endTime.comment:
The endTime of something. For a reserved event or service (e.g. FoodEstablishmentReservation), the time that it is expected to end. For actions that span a period of time, when the action was performed. e.g. John wrote a book from January to December.

Note that Event uses startDate/endDate instead of startTime/endTime, even when describing dates with times. This situation may be clarified in future revisions.
http://schema.org/endTime.label: endTime

http://schema.org/endorsee.comment: A sub property of participant. The person/organization being supported.
http://schema.org/endorsee.label: endorsee

http://schema.org/endorsers.comment: People or organizations that endorse the plan.
http://schema.org/endorsers.label: endorsers

http://schema.org/engineDisplacement.comment:
The volume swept by all of the pistons inside the cylinders of an internal combustion engine in a single movement.

Typical unit code(s): CMQ for cubic centimeter, LTR for liters, INQ for cubic inches * Note 1: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the valueReference property. * Note 2: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.
http://schema.org/engineDisplacement.label: engineDisplacement

http://schema.org/enginePower.comment:
The power of the vehicle's engine. Typical unit code(s): KWT for kilowatt, BHP for brake horsepower, N12 for metric horsepower (PS, with 1 PS = 735,49875 W)

  • Note 1: There are many different ways of measuring an engine's power. For an overview, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Horsepower#Enginepowertest_codes.
  • Note 2: You can link to information about how the given value has been determined using the valueReference property.
  • Note 3: You can use minValue and maxValue to indicate ranges.
http://schema.org/enginePower.label: enginePower

http://schema.org/engineType.comment: The type of engine or engines powering the vehicle.
http://schema.org/engineType.label: engineType

http://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.comment: A sub property of location. The entertainment business where the action occurred.
http://schema.org/entertainmentBusiness.label: entertainmentBusiness

http://schema.org/epidemiology.comment: The characteristics of associated patients, such as age, gender, race etc.
http://schema.org/epidemiology.label: epidemiology

http://schema.org/episode.comment: An episode of a tv, radio or game media within a series or season.
http://schema.org/episode.label: episode

http://schema.org/episodeNumber.comment: Position of the episode within an ordered group of episodes.
http://schema.org/episodeNumber.label: episodeNumber

http://schema.org/episodes.comment: An episode of a TV/radio series or season.
http://schema.org/episodes.label: episodes

http://schema.org/equal.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.
http://schema.org/equal.label: equal

http://schema.org/error.comment: For failed actions, more information on the cause of the failure.
http://schema.org/error.label: error

http://schema.org/estimatedCost.comment: The estimated cost of the supply or supplies consumed when performing instructions.
http://schema.org/estimatedCost.label: estimatedCost

http://schema.org/estimatedFlightDuratio.comment: The estimated time the flight will take.
http://schema.org/estimatedFlightDuratio.label: estimatedFlightDuration

http://schema.org/estimatedSalary.comment: A property describing the estimated salary for a job posting based on a variety of variables including, but not limited to industry, job title, and location. The estimated salary is usually computed by outside organizations and therefore the hiring organization is not bound to this estimated salary.
http://schema.org/estimatedSalary.label: estimatedSalary

http://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.comment: The condition, complication, or symptom whose risk is being estimated.
http://schema.org/estimatesRiskOf.label: estimatesRiskOf

http://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.comment: Statement about ethics policy, e.g. of a NewsMediaOrganization regarding journalistic and publishing practices, or of a Restaurant, a page describing food source policies. In the case of a NewsMediaOrganization, an ethicsPolicy is typically a statement describing the personal, organizational, and corporate standards of behavior expected by the organization.
http://schema.org/ethicsPolicy.label: ethicsPolicy

http://schema.org/event.comment: Upcoming or past event associated with this place, organization, or action.
http://schema.org/event.label: event

http://schema.org/eventSchedule.comment: Associates an Event with a Schedule. There are circumstances where it is preferable to share a schedule for a series of repeating events rather than data on the individual events themselves. For example, a website or application might prefer to publish a schedule for a weekly gym class rather than provide data on every event. A schedule could be processed by applications to add forthcoming events to a calendar. An Event that is associated with a Schedule using this property should not have startDate or endDate properties. These are instead defined within the associated Schedule, this avoids any ambiguity for clients using the data. The propery might have repeated values to specify different schedules, e.g. for different months or seasons.
http://schema.org/eventSchedule.label: eventSchedule

http://schema.org/eventStatus.comment: An eventStatus of an event represents its status; particularly useful when an event is cancelled or rescheduled.
http://schema.org/eventStatus.label: eventStatus

http://schema.org/events.comment: Upcoming or past events associated with this place or organization.
http://schema.org/events.label: events

http://schema.org/evidenceLevel.comment: Strength of evidence of the data used to formulate the guideline (enumerated).
http://schema.org/evidenceLevel.label: evidenceLevel

http://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.comment: Source of the data used to formulate the guidance, e.g. RCT, consensus opinion, etc.
http://schema.org/evidenceOrigin.label: evidenceOrigin

http://schema.org/exampleOfWork.comment: A creative work that this work is an example/instance/realization/derivation of.
http://schema.org/exampleOfWork.label: exampleOfWork

http://schema.org/exceptDate.comment: Defines a Date or DateTime during which a scheduled Event will not take place. The property allows exceptions to a Schedule to be specified. If an exception is specified as a DateTime then only the event that would have started at that specific date and time should be excluded from the schedule. If an exception is specified as a Date then any event that is scheduled for that 24 hour period should be excluded from the schedule. This allows a whole day to be excluded from the schedule without having to itemise every scheduled event.
http://schema.org/exceptDate.label: exceptDate

http://schema.org/exchangeRate.comment: The price of a currency in terms of another currency.
http://schema.org/exchangeRate.label: exchangeRate

http://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.comment: The difference between the price at which a broker or other intermediary buys and sells foreign currency.
http://schema.org/exchangeRateSpread.label: exchangeRateSpread

http://schema.org/executableLibraryName.comment: Library file name e.g., mscorlib.dll, system.web.dll.
http://schema.org/executableLibraryName.label: executableLibraryName

http://schema.org/exerciseCourse.comment: A sub property of location. The course where this action was taken.
http://schema.org/exerciseCourse.label: exerciseCourse

http://schema.org/exercisePlan.comment: A sub property of instrument. The exercise plan used on this action.
http://schema.org/exercisePlan.label: exercisePlan

http://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.comment: A sub property of instrument. The diet used in this action.
http://schema.org/exerciseRelatedDiet.label: exerciseRelatedDiet

http://schema.org/exerciseType.comment: Type(s) of exercise or activity, such as strength training, flexibility training, aerobics, cardiac rehabilitation, etc.
http://schema.org/exerciseType.label: exerciseType

http://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.comment: The earliest date the package may arrive.
http://schema.org/expectedArrivalFrom.label: expectedArrivalFrom

http://schema.org/expectedArrivalUntil.comment: The latest date the package may arrive.
http://schema.org/expectedArrivalUntil.label: expectedArrivalUntil

http://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.comment: The likely outcome in either the short term or long term of the medical condition.
http://schema.org/expectedPrognosis.label: expectedPrognosis

http://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.comment: An Offer which must be accepted before the user can perform the Action. For example, the user may need to buy a movie before being able to watch it.
http://schema.org/expectsAcceptanceOf.label: expectsAcceptanceOf

http://schema.org/experienceRequirements.comment: Description of skills and experience needed for the position.
http://schema.org/experienceRequirements.label: experienceRequirements

http://schema.org/expertConsiderations.comment: Medical expert advice related to the plan.
http://schema.org/expertConsiderations.label: expertConsiderations

http://schema.org/expires.comment: Date the content expires and is no longer useful or available. For example a VideoObject or NewsArticle whose availability or relevance is time-limited, or a ClaimReview fact check whose publisher wants to indicate that it may no longer be relevant (or helpful to highlight) after some date.
http://schema.org/expires.label: expires

http://schema.org/familyName.comment: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of an Person. This can be used along with givenName instead of the name property.
http://schema.org/familyName.label: familyName

http://schema.org/fatContent.comment: The number of grams of fat.
http://schema.org/fatContent.label: fatContent

http://schema.org/featureList.comment: Features or modules provided by this application (and possibly required by other applications).
http://schema.org/featureList.label: featureList

http://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpec.comment: Description of fees, commissions, and other terms applied either to a class of financial product, or by a financial service organization.
http://schema.org/feesAndCommissionsSpec.label: feesAndCommissionsSpecification

http://schema.org/fiberContent.comment: The number of grams of fiber.
http://schema.org/fiberContent.label: fiberContent

http://schema.org/fileFormat.comment: Media type, typically MIME format (see IANA site) of the content e.g. application/zip of a SoftwareApplication binary. In cases where a CreativeWork has several media type representations, 'encoding' can be used to indicate each MediaObject alongside particular fileFormat information. Unregistered or niche file formats can be indicated instead via the most appropriate URL, e.g. defining Web page or a Wikipedia entry.
http://schema.org/fileFormat.label: fileFormat

http://schema.org/fileSize.comment: Size of the application / package (e.g. 18MB). In the absence of a unit (MB, KB etc.), KB will be assumed.
http://schema.org/fileSize.label: fileSize

http://schema.org/firstPerformance.comment: The date and place the work was first performed.
http://schema.org/firstPerformance.label: firstPerformance

http://schema.org/flightNumber.comment: The unique identifier for a flight including the airline IATA code. For example, if describing United flight 110, where the IATA code for United is 'UA', the flightNumber is 'UA110'.
http://schema.org/flightNumber.label: flightNumber

http://schema.org/floorLimit.comment: A floor limit is the amount of money above which credit card transactions must be authorized.
http://schema.org/floorLimit.label: floorLimit

http://schema.org/floorSize.comment:
The size of the accommodation, e.g. in square meter or squarefoot.
Typical unit code(s): MTK for square meter, FTK for square foot, or YDK for square yard
http://schema.org/floorSize.label: floorSize

http://schema.org/followee.comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.
http://schema.org/followee.label: followee

http://schema.org/follows.comment: The most generic uni-directional social relation.
http://schema.org/follows.label: follows

http://schema.org/followup.comment: Typical or recommended followup care after the procedure is performed.
http://schema.org/followup.label: followup

http://schema.org/foodEstablishment.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food establishment where the action occurred.
http://schema.org/foodEstablishment.label: foodEstablishment

http://schema.org/foodEvent.comment: A sub property of location. The specific food event where the action occurred.
http://schema.org/foodEvent.label: foodEvent

http://schema.org/foodWarning.comment: Any precaution, guidance, contraindication, etc. related to consumption of specific foods while taking this drug.
http://schema.org/foodWarning.label: foodWarning

http://schema.org/founder.comment: A person who founded this organization.
http://schema.org/founder.label: founder

http://schema.org/founders.comment: A person who founded this organization.
http://schema.org/founders.label: founders

http://schema.org/foundingDate.comment: The date that this organization was founded.
http://schema.org/foundingDate.label: foundingDate

http://schema.org/foundingLocation.comment: The place where the Organization was founded.
http://schema.org/foundingLocation.label: foundingLocation

http://schema.org/free.comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.
http://schema.org/free.label: free

http://schema.org/frequency.comment: How often the dose is taken, e.g. 'daily'.
http://schema.org/frequency.label: frequency

http://schema.org/fromLocation.comment: A sub property of location. The original location of the object or the agent before the action.
http://schema.org/fromLocation.label: fromLocation

http://schema.org/fuelCapacity.comment:
The capacity of the fuel tank or in the case of electric cars, the battery. If there are multiple components for storage, this should indicate the total of all storage of the same type.

Typical unit code(s): LTR for liters, GLL of US gallons, GLI for UK / imperial gallons, AMH for ampere-hours (for electrical vehicles).
http://schema.org/fuelCapacity.label: fuelCapacity

http://schema.org/fuelConsumption.comment:
The amount of fuel consumed for traveling a particular distance or temporal duration with the given vehicle (e.g. liters per 100 km).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for liters per 100 km. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. L/100 km.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel consumption to another value.
http://schema.org/fuelConsumption.label: fuelConsumption

http://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.comment:
The distance traveled per unit of fuel used; most commonly miles per gallon (mpg) or kilometers per liter (km/L).

  • Note 1: There are unfortunately no standard unit codes for miles per gallon or kilometers per liter. Use unitText to indicate the unit of measurement, e.g. mpg or km/L.
  • Note 2: There are two ways of indicating the fuel consumption, fuelConsumption (e.g. 8 liters per 100 km) and fuelEfficiency (e.g. 30 miles per gallon). They are reciprocal.
  • Note 3: Often, the absolute value is useful only when related to driving speed ("at 80 km/h") or usage pattern ("city traffic"). You can use valueReference to link the value for the fuel economy to another value.
http://schema.org/fuelEfficiency.label: fuelEfficiency

http://schema.org/fuelType.comment: The type of fuel suitable for the engine or engines of the vehicle. If the vehicle has only one engine, this property can be attached directly to the vehicle.
http://schema.org/fuelType.label: fuelType

http://schema.org/functionalClass.comment: The degree of mobility the joint allows.
http://schema.org/functionalClass.label: functionalClass

http://schema.org/funder.comment: A person or organization that supports (sponsors) something through some kind of financial contribution.
http://schema.org/funder.label: funder

http://schema.org/game.comment: Video game which is played on this server.
http://schema.org/game.label: game

http://schema.org/gameItem.comment: An item is an object within the game world that can be collected by a player or, occasionally, a non-player character.
http://schema.org/gameItem.label: gameItem

http://schema.org/gameLocation.comment: Real or fictional location of the game (or part of game).
http://schema.org/gameLocation.label: gameLocation

http://schema.org/gamePlatform.comment: The electronic systems used to play video games.
http://schema.org/gamePlatform.label: gamePlatform

http://schema.org/gameServer.comment: The server on which  it is possible to play the game.
http://schema.org/gameServer.label: gameServer

http://schema.org/gender.comment: Gender of the person. While http://schema.org/Male and http://schema.org/Female may be used, text strings are also acceptable for people who do not identify as a binary gender.
http://schema.org/gender.label: gender

http://schema.org/genre.comment: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.
http://schema.org/genre.label: genre

http://schema.org/geo.comment: The geo coordinates of the place.
http://schema.org/geo.label: geo

http://schema.org/geoMidpoint.comment: Indicates the GeoCoordinates at the centre of a GeoShape e.g. GeoCircle.
http://schema.org/geoMidpoint.label: geoMidpoint

http://schema.org/geoRadius.comment: Indicates the approximate radius of a GeoCircle (metres unless indicated otherwise via Distance notation).
http://schema.org/geoRadius.label: geoRadius

http://schema.org/geographicArea.comment: The geographic area associated with the audience.
http://schema.org/geographicArea.label: geographicArea

http://schema.org/geospatiallyContains.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a containing geometry to a contained geometry. "a contains b iff no points of b lie in the exterior of a, and at least one point of the interior of b lies in the interior of a". As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyContains.label: geospatiallyContains

http://schema.org/geospatiallyCoveredBy.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that covers it. As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyCoveredBy.label: geospatiallyCoveredBy

http://schema.org/geospatiallyCovers.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a covering geometry to a covered geometry. "Every point of b is a point of (the interior or boundary of) a". As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyCovers.label: geospatiallyCovers

http://schema.org/geospatiallyCrosses.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that crosses it: "a crosses b: they have some but not all interior points in common, and the dimension of the intersection is less than that of at least one of them". As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyCrosses.label: geospatiallyCrosses

http://schema.org/geospatiallyDisjoint.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically disjoint: they have no point in common. They form a set of disconnected geometries." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM)
http://schema.org/geospatiallyDisjoint.label: geospatiallyDisjoint

http://schema.org/geospatiallyEquals.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) are topologically equal, as defined in DE-9IM. "Two geometries are topologically equal if their interiors intersect and no part of the interior or boundary of one geometry intersects the exterior of the other" (a symmetric relationship)
http://schema.org/geospatiallyEquals.label: geospatiallyEquals

http://schema.org/geospatiallyIntersects.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) have at least one point in common. As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyIntersects.label: geospatiallyIntersects

http://schema.org/geospatiallyOverlaps.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to another that geospatially overlaps it, i.e. they have some but not all points in common. As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyOverlaps.label: geospatiallyOverlaps

http://schema.org/geospatiallyTouches.comment: Represents spatial relations in which two geometries (or the places they represent) touch: they have at least one boundary point in common, but no interior points." (a symmetric relationship, as defined in DE-9IM )
http://schema.org/geospatiallyTouches.label: geospatiallyTouches

http://schema.org/geospatiallyWithin.comment: Represents a relationship between two geometries (or the places they represent), relating a geometry to one that contains it, i.e. it is inside (i.e. within) its interior. As defined in DE-9IM.
http://schema.org/geospatiallyWithin.label: geospatiallyWithin

http://schema.org/givenName.comment: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person. This can be used along with familyName instead of the name property.
http://schema.org/givenName.label: givenName

http://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.comment: The Global Location Number (GLN, sometimes also referred to as International Location Number or ILN) of the respective organization, person, or place. The GLN is a 13-digit number used to identify parties and physical locations.
http://schema.org/globalLocationNumber.label: globalLocationNumber

http://schema.org/gracePeriod.comment: The period of time after any due date that the borrower has to fulfil its obligations before a default (failure to pay) is deemed to have occurred.
http://schema.org/gracePeriod.label: gracePeriod

http://schema.org/grantee.comment: The person, organization, contact point, or audience that has been granted this permission.
http://schema.org/grantee.label: grantee

http://schema.org/greater.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.
http://schema.org/greater.label: greater

http://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.comment: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.
http://schema.org/greaterOrEqual.label: greaterOrEqual

http://schema.org/gtin12.comment: The GTIN-12 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. The GTIN-12 is the 12-digit GS1 Identification Key composed of a U.P.C. Company Prefix, Item Reference, and Check Digit used to identify trade items. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
http://schema.org/gtin12.label: gtin12

http://schema.org/gtin13.comment: The GTIN-13 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This is equivalent to 13-digit ISBN codes and EAN UCC-13. Former 12-digit UPC codes can be converted into a GTIN-13 code by simply adding a preceeding zero. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
http://schema.org/gtin13.label: gtin13

http://schema.org/gtin14.comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
http://schema.org/gtin14.label: gtin14

http://schema.org/gtin8.comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
http://schema.org/gtin8.label: gtin8

http://schema.org/guideline.comment: A medical guideline related to this entity.
http://schema.org/guideline.label: guideline

http://schema.org/guidelineDate.comment: Date on which this guideline's recommendation was made.
http://schema.org/guidelineDate.label: guidelineDate

http://schema.org/guidelineSubject.comment: The medical conditions, treatments, etc. that are the subject of the guideline.
http://schema.org/guidelineSubject.label: guidelineSubject

http://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.comment: A broadcast channel of a broadcast service.
http://schema.org/hasBroadcastChannel.label: hasBroadcastChannel

http://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.comment: A Category code contained in this code set.
http://schema.org/hasCategoryCode.label: hasCategoryCode

http://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.comment: An offering of the course at a specific time and place or through specific media or mode of study or to a specific section of students.
http://schema.org/hasCourseInstance.label: hasCourseInstance

http://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.comment: Method used for delivery or shipping.
http://schema.org/hasDeliveryMethod.label: hasDeliveryMethod

http://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPerm.comment: A permission related to the access to this document (e.g. permission to read or write an electronic document). For a public document, specify a grantee with an Audience with audienceType equal to "public".
http://schema.org/hasDigitalDocumentPerm.label: hasDigitalDocumentPermission

http://schema.org/hasMap.comment: A URL to a map of the place.
http://schema.org/hasMap.label: hasMap

http://schema.org/hasMenu.comment: Either the actual menu as a structured representation, as text, or a URL of the menu.
http://schema.org/hasMenu.label: hasMenu

http://schema.org/hasMenuItem.comment: A food or drink item contained in a menu or menu section.
http://schema.org/hasMenuItem.label: hasMenuItem

http://schema.org/hasMenuSection.comment: A subgrouping of the menu (by dishes, course, serving time period, etc.).
http://schema.org/hasMenuSection.label: hasMenuSection

http://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.comment: Indicates an OfferCatalog listing for this Organization, Person, or Service.
http://schema.org/hasOfferCatalog.label: hasOfferCatalog

http://schema.org/hasPOS.comment: Points-of-Sales operated by the organization or person.
http://schema.org/hasPOS.label: hasPOS

http://schema.org/hasPart.comment: Indicates a CreativeWork that is (in some sense) a part of this CreativeWork.
http://schema.org/hasPart.label: hasPart

http://schema.org/healthCondition.comment: Specifying the health condition(s) of a patient, medical study, or other target audience.
http://schema.org/healthCondition.label: healthCondition

http://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsuranceO.comment: Whether the coinsurance applies before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?
http://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsuranceO.label: healthPlanCoinsuranceOption

http://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsuranceR.comment: Whether The rate of coinsurance expressed as a number between 0.0 and 1.0.
http://schema.org/healthPlanCoinsuranceR.label: healthPlanCoinsuranceRate

http://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.comment: Whether the copay is before or after deductible, etc. TODO: Is this a closed set?
http://schema.org/healthPlanCopayOption.label: healthPlanCopayOption

http://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.comment: Whether The costs to the patient for services under this network or formulary.
http://schema.org/healthPlanCostSharing.label: healthPlanCostSharing

http://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.comment: The tier(s) of drugs offered by this formulary or insurance plan.
http://schema.org/healthPlanDrugTier.label: healthPlanDrugTier

http://schema.org/healthPlanId.comment: The 14-character, HIOS-generated Plan ID number. (Plan IDs must be unique, even across different markets.)
http://schema.org/healthPlanId.label: healthPlanId

http://schema.org/healthPlanMarketingUrl.comment: The URL that goes directly to the plan brochure for the specific standard plan or plan variation.
http://schema.org/healthPlanMarketingUrl.label: healthPlanMarketingUrl

http://schema.org/healthPlanNetworkId.comment: Name or unique ID of network. (Networks are often reused across different insurance plans).
http://schema.org/healthPlanNetworkId.label: healthPlanNetworkId

http://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCate.comment: The category or type of pharmacy associated with this cost sharing.
http://schema.org/healthPlanPharmacyCate.label: healthPlanPharmacyCategory

http://schema.org/highPrice.comment: The highest price of all offers available.
http://schema.org/highPrice.label: highPrice

http://schema.org/homeLocation.comment: A contact location for a person's residence.
http://schema.org/homeLocation.label: homeLocation

http://schema.org/homeTeam.comment: The home team in a sports event.
http://schema.org/homeTeam.label: homeTeam

http://schema.org/honorificPrefix.comment: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.
http://schema.org/honorificPrefix.label: honorificPrefix

http://schema.org/honorificSuffix.comment: An honorific suffix preceding a Person's name such as M.D. /PhD/MSCSW.
http://schema.org/honorificSuffix.label: honorificSuffix

http://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.comment: A hospital with which the physician or office is affiliated.
http://schema.org/hospitalAffiliation.label: hospitalAffiliation

http://schema.org/hostingOrganization.comment: The organization (airline, travelers' club, etc.) the membership is made with.
http://schema.org/hostingOrganization.label: hostingOrganization

http://schema.org/hoursAvailable.comment: The hours during which this service or contact is available.
http://schema.org/hoursAvailable.label: hoursAvailable

http://schema.org/httpMethod.comment: An HTTP method that specifies the appropriate HTTP method for a request to an HTTP EntryPoint. Values are capitalized strings as used in HTTP.
http://schema.org/httpMethod.label: httpMethod

http://schema.org/iataCode.comment: IATA identifier for an airline or airport.
http://schema.org/iataCode.label: iataCode

http://schema.org/identifier.comment: The identifier property represents any kind of identifier for any kind of Thing, such as ISBNs, GTIN codes, UUIDs etc. Schema.org provides dedicated properties for representing many of these, either as textual strings or as URL (URI) links. See background notes for more details.
http://schema.org/identifier.label: identifier

http://schema.org/identifyingExam.comment: A physical examination that can identify this sign.
http://schema.org/identifyingExam.label: identifyingExam

http://schema.org/identifyingTest.comment: A diagnostic test that can identify this sign.
http://schema.org/identifyingTest.label: identifyingTest

http://schema.org/image.comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.
http://schema.org/image.label: image

http://schema.org/inAlbum.comment: The album to which this recording belongs.
http://schema.org/inAlbum.label: inAlbum

http://schema.org/inCodeSet.comment: A CategoryCodeSet that contains this catagory code.
http://schema.org/inCodeSet.label: inCodeSet

http://schema.org/inLanguage.comment: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.
http://schema.org/inLanguage.label: inLanguage

http://schema.org/inPlaylist.comment: The playlist to which this recording belongs.
http://schema.org/inPlaylist.label: inPlaylist

http://schema.org/inSupportOf.comment: Qualification, candidature, degree, application that Thesis supports.
http://schema.org/inSupportOf.label: inSupportOf

http://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.
http://schema.org/incentiveCompensation.label: incentiveCompensation

http://schema.org/incentives.comment: Description of bonus and commission compensation aspects of the job.
http://schema.org/incentives.label: incentives

http://schema.org/includedComposition.comment: Smaller compositions included in this work (e.g. a movement in a symphony).
http://schema.org/includedComposition.label: includedComposition

http://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset (this property was previously 'catalog', preferred name is now 'includedInDataCatalog').
http://schema.org/includedDataCatalog.label: includedDataCatalog

http://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.comment: A data catalog which contains this dataset.
http://schema.org/includedInDataCatalog.label: includedInDataCatalog

http://schema.org/includedInHealthInsura.comment: The insurance plans that cover this drug.
http://schema.org/includedInHealthInsura.label: includedInHealthInsurancePlan

http://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.comment: A modifiable or non-modifiable risk factor included in the calculation, e.g. age, coexisting condition.
http://schema.org/includedRiskFactor.label: includedRiskFactor

http://schema.org/includesObject.comment: This links to a node or nodes indicating the exact quantity of the products included in the offer.
http://schema.org/includesObject.label: includesObject

http://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.comment: The condition, complication, etc. influenced by this factor.
http://schema.org/increasesRiskOf.label: increasesRiskOf

http://schema.org/indication.comment: A factor that indicates use of this therapy for treatment and/or prevention of a condition, symptom, etc. For therapies such as drugs, indications can include both officially-approved indications as well as off-label uses. These can be distinguished by using the ApprovedIndication subtype of MedicalIndication.
http://schema.org/indication.label: indication

http://schema.org/industry.comment: The industry associated with the job position.
http://schema.org/industry.label: industry

http://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.comment:
The ISO 3166-1 (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2) or ISO 3166-2 code, the place, or the GeoShape for the geo-political region(s) for which the offer or delivery charge specification is not valid, e.g. a region where the transaction is not allowed.

See also eligibleRegion.
http://schema.org/ineligibleRegion.label: ineligibleRegion

http://schema.org/infectiousAgent.comment: The actual infectious agent, such as a specific bacterium.
http://schema.org/infectiousAgent.label: infectiousAgent

http://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.comment: The class of infectious agent (bacteria, prion, etc.) that causes the disease.
http://schema.org/infectiousAgentClass.label: infectiousAgentClass

http://schema.org/ingredients.comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.
http://schema.org/ingredients.label: ingredients

http://schema.org/inker.comment: The individual who traces over the pencil drawings in ink after pencils are complete.
http://schema.org/inker.label: inker

http://schema.org/insertion.comment: The place of attachment of a muscle, or what the muscle moves.
http://schema.org/insertion.label: insertion

http://schema.org/installUrl.comment: URL at which the app may be installed, if different from the URL of the item.
http://schema.org/installUrl.label: installUrl

http://schema.org/instructor.comment: A person assigned to instruct or provide instructional assistance for the CourseInstance.
http://schema.org/instructor.label: instructor

http://schema.org/instrument.comment: The object that helped the agent perform the action. e.g. John wrote a book with a pen.
http://schema.org/instrument.label: instrument

http://schema.org/intensity.comment: Quantitative measure gauging the degree of force involved in the exercise, for example, heartbeats per minute. May include the velocity of the movement.
http://schema.org/intensity.label: intensity

http://schema.org/interactingDrug.comment: Another drug that is known to interact with this drug in a way that impacts the effect of this drug or causes a risk to the patient. Note: disease interactions are typically captured as contraindications.
http://schema.org/interactingDrug.label: interactingDrug

http://schema.org/interactionCount.comment: This property is deprecated, alongside the UserInteraction types on which it depended.
http://schema.org/interactionCount.label: interactionCount

http://schema.org/interactionService.comment: The WebSite or SoftwareApplication where the interactions took place.
http://schema.org/interactionService.label: interactionService

http://schema.org/interactionStatistic.comment: The number of interactions for the CreativeWork using the WebSite or SoftwareApplication. The most specific child type of InteractionCounter should be used.
http://schema.org/interactionStatistic.label: interactionStatistic

http://schema.org/interactionType.comment: The Action representing the type of interaction. For up votes, +1s, etc. use LikeAction. For down votes use DislikeAction. Otherwise, use the most specific Action.
http://schema.org/interactionType.label: interactionType

http://schema.org/interactivityType.comment: The predominant mode of learning supported by the learning resource. Acceptable values are 'active', 'expositive', or 'mixed'.
http://schema.org/interactivityType.label: interactivityType

http://schema.org/interestRate.comment: The interest rate, charged or paid, applicable to the financial product. Note: This is different from the calculated annualPercentageRate.
http://schema.org/interestRate.label: interestRate

http://schema.org/inventoryLevel.comment: The current approximate inventory level for the item or items.
http://schema.org/inventoryLevel.label: inventoryLevel

http://schema.org/inverseOf.comment: Relates a property to a property that is its inverse. Inverse properties relate the same pairs of items to each other, but in reversed direction. For example, the 'alumni' and 'alumniOf' properties are inverseOf each other. Some properties don't have explicit inverses; in these situations RDFa and JSON-LD syntax for reverse properties can be used.
http://schema.org/inverseOf.label: inverseOf

http://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatients.comment: Whether the provider is accepting new patients.
http://schema.org/isAcceptingNewPatients.label: isAcceptingNewPatients

http://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.comment: A flag to signal that the item, event, or place is accessible for free.
http://schema.org/isAccessibleForFree.label: isAccessibleForFree

http://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePart.comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is an accessory or spare part.
http://schema.org/isAccessoryOrSparePart.label: isAccessoryOrSparePartFor

http://schema.org/isAvailableGenerically.comment: True if the drug is available in a generic form (regardless of name).
http://schema.org/isAvailableGenerically.label: isAvailableGenerically

http://schema.org/isBasedOn.comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.
http://schema.org/isBasedOn.label: isBasedOn

http://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.comment: A resource that was used in the creation of this resource. This term can be repeated for multiple sources. For example, http://example.com/great-multiplication-intro.html.
http://schema.org/isBasedOnUrl.label: isBasedOnUrl

http://schema.org/isConsumableFor.comment: A pointer to another product (or multiple products) for which this product is a consumable.
http://schema.org/isConsumableFor.label: isConsumableFor

http://schema.org/isFamilyFriendly.comment: Indicates whether this content is family friendly.
http://schema.org/isFamilyFriendly.label: isFamilyFriendly

http://schema.org/isGift.comment: Was the offer accepted as a gift for someone other than the buyer.
http://schema.org/isGift.label: isGift

http://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.comment: True is the broadcast is of a live event.
http://schema.org/isLiveBroadcast.label: isLiveBroadcast

http://schema.org/isPartOf.comment: Indicates a CreativeWork that this CreativeWork is (in some sense) part of.
http://schema.org/isPartOf.label: isPartOf

http://schema.org/isProprietary.comment: True if this item's name is a proprietary/brand name (vs. generic name).
http://schema.org/isProprietary.label: isProprietary

http://schema.org/isRelatedTo.comment: A pointer to another, somehow related product (or multiple products).
http://schema.org/isRelatedTo.label: isRelatedTo

http://schema.org/isSimilarTo.comment: A pointer to another, functionally similar product (or multiple products).
http://schema.org/isSimilarTo.label: isSimilarTo

http://schema.org/isVariantOf.comment: A pointer to a base product from which this product is a variant. It is safe to infer that the variant inherits all product features from the base model, unless defined locally. This is not transitive.
http://schema.org/isVariantOf.label: isVariantOf

http://schema.org/isicV4.comment: The International Standard of Industrial Classification of All Economic Activities (ISIC), Revision 4 code for a particular organization, business person, or place.
http://schema.org/isicV4.label: isicV4

http://schema.org/isrcCode.comment: The International Standard Recording Code for the recording.
http://schema.org/isrcCode.label: isrcCode

http://schema.org/issn.comment: The International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) that identifies this serial publication. You can repeat this property to identify different formats of, or the linking ISSN (ISSN-L) for, this serial publication.
http://schema.org/issn.label: issn

http://schema.org/issueNumber.comment: Identifies the issue of publication; for example, "iii" or "2".
http://schema.org/issueNumber.label: issueNumber

http://schema.org/issuedBy.comment: The organization issuing the ticket or permit.
http://schema.org/issuedBy.label: issuedBy

http://schema.org/issuedThrough.comment: The service through with the permit was granted.
http://schema.org/issuedThrough.label: issuedThrough

http://schema.org/iswcCode.comment: The International Standard Musical Work Code for the composition.
http://schema.org/iswcCode.label: iswcCode

http://schema.org/item.comment: An entity represented by an entry in a list or data feed (e.g. an 'artist' in a list of 'artists')’.
http://schema.org/item.label: item

http://schema.org/itemCondition.comment: A predefined value from OfferItemCondition or a textual description of the condition of the product or service, or the products or services included in the offer.
http://schema.org/itemCondition.label: itemCondition

http://schema.org/itemListElement.comment:
For itemListElement values, you can use simple strings (e.g. "Peter", "Paul", "Mary"), existing entities, or use ListItem.

Text values are best if the elements in the list are plain strings. Existing entities are best for a simple, unordered list of existing things in your data. ListItem is used with ordered lists when you want to provide additional context about the element in that list or when the same item might be in different places in different lists.

Note: The order of elements in your mark-up is not sufficient for indicating the order or elements. Use ListItem with a 'position' property in such cases.
http://schema.org/itemListElement.label: itemListElement

http://schema.org/itemListOrder.comment: Type of ordering (e.g. Ascending, Descending, Unordered).
http://schema.org/itemListOrder.label: itemListOrder

http://schema.org/itemReviewed.comment: The item that is being reviewed/rated.
http://schema.org/itemReviewed.label: itemReviewed

http://schema.org/jobBenefits.comment: Description of benefits associated with the job.
http://schema.org/jobBenefits.label: jobBenefits

http://schema.org/jobLocation.comment: A (typically single) geographic location associated with the job position.
http://schema.org/jobLocation.label: jobLocation

http://schema.org/jobTitle.comment: The job title of the person (for example, Financial Manager).
http://schema.org/jobTitle.label: jobTitle

http://schema.org/keywords.comment: Keywords or tags used to describe this content. Multiple entries in a keywords list are typically delimited by commas.
http://schema.org/keywords.label: keywords

http://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.comment: A textual description of known damages, both repaired and unrepaired.
http://schema.org/knownVehicleDamages.label: knownVehicleDamages

http://schema.org/knows.comment: The most generic bi-directional social/work relation.
http://schema.org/knows.label: knows

http://schema.org/labelDetails.comment: Link to the drug's label details.
http://schema.org/labelDetails.label: labelDetails

http://schema.org/landlord.comment: A sub property of participant. The owner of the real estate property.
http://schema.org/landlord.label: landlord

http://schema.org/language.comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.
http://schema.org/language.label: language

http://schema.org/lastReviewed.comment: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.
http://schema.org/lastReviewed.label: lastReviewed

http://schema.org/latitude.comment: The latitude of a location. For example 37.42242 (WGS 84).
http://schema.org/latitude.label: latitude

http://schema.org/learningResourceType.comment: The predominant type or kind characterizing the learning resource. For example, 'presentation', 'handout'.
http://schema.org/learningResourceType.label: learningResourceType

http://schema.org/legalName.comment: The official name of the organization, e.g. the registered company name.
http://schema.org/legalName.label: legalName

http://schema.org/legalStatus.comment: The drug or supplement's legal status, including any controlled substance schedules that apply.
http://schema.org/legalStatus.label: legalStatus

http://schema.org/legislationAppliedBy.comment: Indicates that this legislation (or part of a legislation) is somehow transfered by another legislation in a different legislative context. This is an informative link, and it has no legal value. For legally-binding links of transposition, use the property legislationTransposedBy.
